    42	## 3. Session Lifecycle
    43	
    44	```
    45	created ──► active ──► suspended ──► active   (resume)
    46	                    └──► expired               (TTL exceeded while suspended, or explicit expiry)
    47	
    48	active ──► expired                             (explicit expiry while active)
    49	```
    50	
    51	| State | Meaning |
    52	|---|---|
    53	| `created` | Initialized but no message processed yet. |
    54	| `active` | At least one message processed; within activity TTL. |
    55	| `suspended` | No activity within TTL; may be resumed. Memory is preserved. |
    56	| `expired` | Permanently closed. Memory may be archived per policy. |
    57	
    58	State transitions are recorded with a timestamp. Sessions does not automatically expire sessions on a timer; it marks sessions stale when queried or when the caller explicitly invokes `sessionStore.expire()`.
