     1	# v1 Core Spec — `@relay-assistant/core`
     2	
     3	**Status:** IMPLEMENTATION_READY
     4	**Date:** 2026-04-11
     5	**Package:** `@relay-assistant/core`
     6	**Version target:** v0.1.0 (pre-1.0, provisional)
     7	
     8	---
     9	
    10	## 1. Responsibilities
    11	
    12	`@relay-assistant/core` is the root composition layer. Every other package in this SDK depends on contracts exported from core; core depends on nothing else in this monorepo.
    13	
    14	**Owns:**
    15	- `AssistantDefinition` — the declarative config struct describing an assistant's identity, capabilities, and runtime constraints
    16	- `AssistantRuntime` — the live object returned by `createAssistant()`; holds registered subsystems and drives the main event loop
    17	- Capability registration — typed registry mapping capability names to handler functions
    18	- Lifecycle hooks — `onStart`, `onStop`, `onMessage`, `onError` (synchronous signatures; async adapters are the caller's responsibility)
    19	- Inbound message normalization — converts raw relay-layer events into the canonical `InboundMessage` type before routing to handlers
    20	- Health/readiness probe — `runtime.status()` returns a structured object suitable for a health endpoint
    21	
    22	**Does NOT own:**
    23	- Session state (→ `@relay-assistant/sessions`)
    24	- Surface I/O (→ `@relay-assistant/surfaces`)
    25	- Memory retrieval or storage (→ `@relay-assistant/memory`)
    26	- Model selection or routing (→ `@relay-assistant/routing`)
    27	- Multi-agent coordination (→ `@relay-assistant/coordination`)
    28	- Any transport protocol, HTTP server, or relay socket management (→ relay foundation layer)
    29	
    30	---
    31	
    32	## 2. Non-Goals
    33	
    34	- Core does not start a web server, open sockets, or manage relay connections. Those belong to the relay foundation beneath this SDK.
    35	- Core does not implement retry logic, queue management, or delivery guarantees. Those are relay-layer concerns.
    36	- Core is not an orchestrator. It registers capabilities and dispatches events; it does not sequence multi-step workflows.
    37	- Core does not enforce action policy (→ `@relay-assistant/policy`).
    38	- Core does not know about cloud infrastructure. All interfaces must be implementable by a self-hosted consumer without any private service.
    39	
    40	---
    41	
    42	## 3. Interfaces and Contracts
    43	
    44	### 3.1 `AssistantDefinition`
    45	
    46	```typescript
    47	export interface AssistantDefinition {
    48	  /** Unique identifier for this assistant. Stable across restarts. */
    49	  id: string;
    50	
    51	  /** Human-readable display name. Used in surface headers and logs. */
    52	  name: string;
    53	
    54	  /**
    55	   * Optional description. Surfaced in admin UIs and capability registries.
    56	   * Not used at runtime.
    57	   */
    58	  description?: string;
    59	
    60	  /**
    61	   * Named capability handlers. Keys are capability names; values are handler
    62	   * functions. Core dispatches inbound messages to handlers by capability name.
    63	   */
    64	  capabilities: Record<string, CapabilityHandler>;
    65	
    66	  /**
    67	   * Lifecycle hooks. All optional. Called synchronously (handlers may return
    68	   * promises, but core does not await them unless noted).
    69	   */
    70	  hooks?: AssistantHooks;
    71	
    72	  /**
    73	   * Runtime constraints. Used by routing and scheduling layers; core
    74	   * validates structure but does not enforce values.
    75	   */
    76	  constraints?: RuntimeConstraints;
    77	}
    78	```
    79	
    80	### 3.2 `CapabilityHandler`
    81	
    82	```typescript
    83	export type CapabilityHandler = (
    84	  message: InboundMessage,
    85	  context: CapabilityContext,
    86	) => Promise<void> | void;
    87	```
    88	
    89	### 3.3 `InboundMessage`
    90	
    91	```typescript
    92	export interface InboundMessage {
    93	  /** Relay-assigned message ID. Globally unique. */
    94	  id: string;
    95	
    96	  /** Surface this message arrived on. Opaque string; not parsed by core. */
    97	  surfaceId: string;
    98	
    99	  /** Session this message belongs to. May be undefined for sessionless surfaces. */
   100	  sessionId?: string;
   101	
   102	  /** Normalized text body. Core does not parse further. */
   103	  text: string;
   104	
   105	  /**
   106	   * Original relay payload. Core preserves this verbatim so capability
   107	   * handlers can access surface-specific fields without core needing to
   108	   * understand them.
   109	   */
   110	  raw: unknown;
   111	
   112	  /** ISO-8601 timestamp of message receipt at the relay layer. */
   113	  receivedAt: string;
   114	
   115	  /** Name of the capability this message was dispatched to. Set by core. */
   116	  capability: string;
   117	}
   118	```
   119	
   120	### 3.4 `CapabilityContext`
   121	
   122	```typescript
   123	export interface CapabilityContext {
   124	  /** The live AssistantRuntime. Handlers may call runtime.emit() to send responses. */
   125	  runtime: AssistantRuntime;
   126	
   127	  /**
   128	   * Logger bound to this invocation. Structured; always includes messageId,
   129	   * capability, and surfaceId.
   130	   */
   131	  log: ContextLogger;
   132	}
   133	```
   134	
   135	### 3.5 `AssistantHooks`
   136	
   137	```typescript
   138	export interface AssistantHooks {
   139	  /** Called once after createAssistant() completes subsystem registration. */
   140	  onStart?: (runtime: AssistantRuntime) => Promise<void> | void;
   141	
   142	  /** Called once when runtime.stop() is invoked. */
   143	  onStop?: (runtime: AssistantRuntime) => Promise<void> | void;
   144	
   145	  /**
   146	   * Called before dispatching any inbound message to a capability handler.
   147	   * Return false to drop the message without processing.
   148	   */
   149	  onMessage?: (message: InboundMessage) => boolean | Promise<boolean>;
   150	
   151	  /** Called when a capability handler throws. */
   152	  onError?: (error: Error, message: InboundMessage) => void;
   153	}
   154	```
   155	
   156	### 3.6 `RuntimeConstraints`
   157	
   158	```typescript
   159	export interface RuntimeConstraints {
   160	  /**
   161	   * Maximum time (ms) core will wait for a capability handler to resolve.
   162	   * Defaults to 30000. Core emits a timeout error and calls onError if exceeded.
   163	   */
   164	  handlerTimeoutMs?: number;
   165	
   166	  /**
   167	   * Maximum concurrent capability invocations. Defaults to 10.
   168	   * Core queues messages beyond this limit; does not drop them.
   169	   */
   170	  maxConcurrentHandlers?: number;
   171	}
   172	```
   173	
   174	### 3.7 `AssistantRuntime`
   175	
   176	```typescript
   177	export interface AssistantRuntime {
   178	  /** The definition this runtime was created from. Frozen after creation. */
   179	  readonly definition: Readonly<AssistantDefinition>;
   180	
   181	  /**
   182	   * Emit an outbound event. Core passes this to registered surface adapters;
   183	   * the relay layer handles actual delivery.
   184	   */
   185	  emit(event: OutboundEvent): Promise<void>;
   186	
   187	  /**
   188	   * Dispatch a message directly (bypasses relay; useful for testing).
   189	   * Runs the full dispatch pipeline including hooks.
   190	   */
   191	  dispatch(message: InboundMessage): Promise<void>;
   192	
   193	  /**
   194	   * Register a subsystem at runtime. Called by other packages during their
   195	   * initialization. Returns the runtime for chaining.
   196	   */
   197	  register<T>(name: string, subsystem: T): AssistantRuntime;
   198	
   199	  /**
   200	   * Retrieve a registered subsystem. Throws if not found.
   201	   */
   202	  get<T>(name: string): T;
